OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCuba votes to legalise     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsame-sex marriage          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Cuba has voted to legalise same-sex    
OL,6, marriage in a national referendum.     
OL,8,FAbout two-thirds of the population     
OL,9,Fvoted to approve reforms in a new      
OL,10,FFamily Code, which will also allow     
OL,11,Fsurrogate pregnancies and give gay     
OL,12,Fcouples the right to adopt children.   
OL,14,FIt marks a big moment for Cuba, which  
OL,15,Fsaw gay people persecuted and sent to  
OL,16,Fwork camps in the 1960s and 70s.       
OL,18,FHowever, there was significant         
OL,19,Fopposition to the reforms among        
OL,20,Freligious groups and conservatives.    
